stimulusHtml: At time t = 10 minutes, water begins draining from the tank at a rate modeled by the function D, where  D( t )=10 e ( sint )/10 MathType@MTEF@5@5@@44D0@  liters per minute. Water continues to drain at this rate until time t = 55 minutes. How many liters of water are in the tank at time t = 55 minutes?

features.html: At time t = 0 minutes, a tank contains 100 liters of water. The piecewise-linear graph above shows the rate R(t), in liters per minute, at which water is pumped into the tank during a 55-minute period.
